modules.description: Provides functions to configure HTTP server behavior, including buffer size, error handling, response headers, message type, and subprotocol selection. Works with custom types for error handling, headers, and subprotocol logic. Used to initialize and customize server instances for specific WebSocket communication requirements.

Provides asynchronous HTTP server and client operations, including request handling, response generation, and connection management. Works with raw byte streams, HTTP messages, and connection states. Used to build custom HTTP services, proxy servers, and integrations with other asynchronous systems.

Configures and customizes HTTP server behavior for WebSocket communication through specific types for errors, headers, and subprotocols. Offers control over buffer sizes, response formatting, and message handling to tailor server interactions. Allows setting custom error responses, defining header structures, and selecting subprotocols during initialization. Enables precise server setup for diverse WebSocket application needs.
